            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgd700\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgd700', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Aztec Sun Stone on display at the National Museum of Anthropology in Mexico City (<htcite0> ; <htcite1>).<br />Photo taken on <htdate0>, during a visit to the Museum.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>First Steps (Volume 1): Mesoamerican calendars (<htcite2>)</li><li>First Steps (Volume 1): Understanding the Multiplication Table (6 and 7) (<htcite3>)</li><li>History: Cradles of civilization (Part I) (<htcite4>)</li><li>Who truly discovered America (<i>Abya Yala</i>)? (Who... ?)</li><li>Mathematical Games: Building to count (Suanpan, 算盤) (<htcite5>)</li><li>Mathematical Games: Exercising with numbers (<htcite6>)</li><li>Mathematical Games: Multiplying with the body (Level 1) (<htcite7>)</li><li>Mathematical Games: Walking and singing (<htcite8>)</li><li>Together we are strong (Universe)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">2 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgHs3\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgHs3', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Mammoth fossil exhibited in Mexico. Photograph taken on <htdate0>, during a visit to the National Museum of Anthropology in Mexico ().</div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">3 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"mamut\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('mamut', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\"></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">4 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgOaxaca\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgOaxaca', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\"></div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
